content:
Create an Event Monitoring Analytics app and configure it to incrementally add new event log file data since the last dataset update. This configuration reduces the likelihood of reaching row count limits and your 24 hourly rolling upload limit, and speeds up dataset refreshes for large datasets.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions
Requires Salesforce Shield or Event Monitoring add-on subscriptions

To use Event Monitoring Analytics apps:
Use CRM Analytics Templated Apps
To create and manage Event Monitoring Analytics apps:
Access Event Monitoring Analytics Templates and Apps
Manage CRM Analytics Templated Apps
Edit CRM Analytics Dataflows

Enable Add only new event log file data to existing datasets? setting
Name your app
Click Create

After creation, share the app with other users in your org.
Only users with Manage CRM Analytics Templated Apps and Access Event Monitoring Analytics Templates and Apps permissions can see the app.

Event log files have a 24-hour generation period. Incrementally refreshing data means that apps accrue data daily over the 30-day retention period starting the first day they're created.

Schedule your dataflows to run daily.

Considerations for Incremental Refreshes to Event Monitoring Analytics App Datasets:

* Keep these considerations in mind when configuring your app to incrementally refresh datasets.
title: Create Event Monitoring Analytics App with Incremental Refresh
